headline: Fed cuts rates as dissents loom at key December meeting
summary: The Federal Reserve, as widely expected, delivered a 25-percentage-point cut at its Dec. 10 Federal Open Market Committee meeting — its third reduction of 2025 — trimming the target range to roughly 3.50% to 3.75%. headline: Stock of Exchange Operator Behind FedWatch Tool Faces Long Losing Streak
summary: CME Group stock is in the doldrums. Shares of the exchange operator—whose FedWatch tool tracks the probabilities of future Federal Reserve interest-rate changes—have fallen about 4.6% over the past eight trading days.
